title: [Old Ta'Faendryl, East]
description: The road here is wide, bounded to the east by the height of the city wall, and to the west by a series of shattered towers.  The ruins of several long low buildings form dark mounds beneath the slender silhouettes of the towers.

The road here is wide, bounded to the east by the height of the city wall, and to the west by a series of shattered towers.  Several ruined barracks crouch in the slender shadows of the towers, like dogs cowering beneath a scolding finger.
